===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|countable|uncountable}} A [[powdered]] substance that develops strong [[adhesive]] properties when mixed with [[water]].
#* {{quote-book|author=W[illiam] B[abington] Maxwell|authorlink=W. B. Maxwell|chapter=22|title=The Mirror and the Lamp|location=London; New York, NY.|publisher=[[w:Cassell (publisher)|Cassell]]|year=1918|oclc=4293073|ol=1097634W|passage=In the autumn there was a row at some '''cement''' works about the unskilled labour men. A union had just been started for them and all but a few joined. One of these blacklegs was laid for by a picket and knocked out of time.}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The [[paste]]-like substance resulting from mixing such a powder with water, or the [[rock]]-like substance that forms when it dries.
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} Any material with strong [[adhesive]] properties.
# {{lb|en|figurative}} A [[bond]] of [[union]]; that which [[unite]]s [[firmly]], as persons in friendship or in society.
#: {{ux|en|the '''cement''' of our love}}
# {{lb|en|anatomy}} The [[layer]] of [[bone]] investing the [[root]] and [[neck]] of a [[tooth]]; [[cementum]].

